properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 7 at 1:57PM PST until February 10 at 1:04AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Cedar River Near Landsburg affecting King County
Cedar River At Renton affecting King County
Nisqually River At McKenna affecting Pierce and Thurston Counties
Green River Near Auburn affecting King County

River basins continue to drain. Dam operators continue to make
regulation adjustments as they manage inflow and flood pools in the
reservoirs. Here are some updated river forecasts.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Cedar River Near Landsburg
* Until late Sunday night.
* At  1:00 PM Friday the stage was 7.8 feet.
* Flood stage is 5.7 feet.
* Major flooding is occurring and Major flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will continue to rise and crest near 7.8 feet
around 4 PM Friday. The river will fall below flood stage Sunday
afternoon.
* Impact...At 7.5 feet, the Cedar River will cause severe flooding
from Landsburg downstream through Maplewood. Deep and swift flood
waters will inundate many roads and some residential areas...
especially in Maple Valley.  Flooding will occur all along the
river including headwaters...tributaries...and other streams
within and near the Cedar River Basin.  A stage of 7.5 feet on
the Cedar River corresponds to a phase 4 flood in the King County
flood system.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.

NWSheadline: Flood Warning extended until late Sunday night
